China Tin Says Teams Up With Chinalco, Grirem for Rare Earths

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-28T09:09:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/china-tin-says-teams-up-with-chinalco-grirem-for-rare-earths.html
China Tin Group Co. , the country’s
second-largest maker, signed an agreement with Aluminum Corp. of
 China  and Grirem Advanced Materials Co. to develop rare-earth
resources in Guangxi, according to a statement.  The company will set up a joint venture with Chinalco, as
Aluminum Corp. of China is also known, and Grirem Advanced
Materials, a rare-earth mining company, according to the
 statement  posted on its website today, without giving details.  China is the world’s biggest exporter of rare earths, which
are 17 chemically similar elements.  -- Helen Sun . Editors: Jake Lloyd-Smith, Jarrett Banks  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helen Sun in Shanghai at 
 hsun30@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Poole at 
 jpoole4@bloomberg.net  